'''Ethics''' (from the [[Ancient Greek]] ''ἠθικός'' or "ethikos" meaning "Theory of living") is one of the five major branches of [[philosophy]], which attempts distinguish that which is [[right]] from that which is [[wrong]]. Ethics differs from morality in that morality allows more leeway for individual interpretation whereas ethics tend to be more global. The [[Western philosophy|Western tradition]] of ethics is sometimes called '''moral philosophy'''. Ethics in plain words means studying and analyzing right from wrong; [[good and bad|good from bad]].
